Leaf relative water content (RWC) was measured as described earlier50. Briefly, the leaf fragments of nearly same length and area were excised and fresh weight (FW) was measured immediately. Leaf fragments were hydrated to full turgidity by floating them on deionized water for 6 h, blotted on paper towel and the turgid weight (TW) was measured. Leaf fragments were then dried in hot air oven at 80 °C for 72 h and weighed to determine the dry weight (DW). The per cent RWC was calculated as\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
