				\begin{document}$${\rm{RWC}}( \% )=({\rm{FW}}-{\rm{DW}})/({\rm{TW}}-{\rm{DW}})\times 100.$$\end{document}RWC(%)=(FW−DW)/(TW−DW)×100.

The leaf fragments (1 cm2) were harvested and rinsed in deionized water to remove the solutes leaked at the cut ends and then incubated in deionized water for 8 h at 25 °C under constant shaking (25 rpm). The conductivity of electrolytes leaked into bathing medium from stressed leaf samples was recorded (T1) using EC-TDS analyzer (CM183, Elico-India). Subsequently, leaf fragments were boiled for 30 min, and a final reading was recorded (T2) after cooling to room temperature. Similarly, conductivity was also measured for leaf segments from well-watered plants (C1 and C2). The cell membrane stability was calculated as described previously51 using the formula\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
